('14413fcefc273a7288c66bcd334898d55b1ce02c', '2014-02-26', '2014-02-27', 'Legals', '\n    <P><B> City of Polk City </B></P><P><B> Budget Work Session </B></P><P><B> February 10, 2014 </B></P><P> The City Council for the City of Polk City met in special session on February 10, 2014, at City Hall in Polk City, Iowa. Present were David Dvorak, Jeff Walters, Dan Lane and Ron Anderson. Robert Mordini was absent. Also present were Administrator Gary Mahannah, Finance Officer Deb Nabity and Department Heads. Mayor Jason Morse called the meeting to order at 5:00 p.m.</P><P>A quick overview of the 2014-2015 budget was given. Police answered questions specifically asked about the purchase of new guns. Council discussed an increase of 5% in both water and sewer rates, a reduction of $100,000 in street repair, removing the purchase of a new dump truck and fire truck and placing them in the following fiscal year, and removing $100,000 for slip lining sewer lines. The council discussed keeping the Booth/Washington Street Project moving forward and funding it in the 2013-2014 budget to get the project started.</P><P>Mayor Morse adjourned the meeting at 6:20 p.m.</P><P>Jason Morse, Mayor</P><P>ATTEST:</P><P>Gary Mahannah, City Administrator</P><P>Published in the Ankeny Register on February 21, 2014 </P>\n  '),
