('15ecc405bcc015e2d64731947456e81385f19314', '2014-02-26', '2014-02-27', 'Legals', '\n    <P><B> 118 - City of Ankeny </B></P><P><B> NOTICE OF MEETING OF THE COUNCIL OF THE CITY OF ANKENY, STATE OF IOWA, ON THE MATTER OF THE PROPOSED ISSUANCE OF NOT TO EXCEED $450,000 PRINCIPAL AMOUNT OF GENERAL OBLIGATION BONDS, SERIES 2014 (FOR A GENERAL CORPORATE PURPOSE), AND HEARING ON ISSUANCE OF BONDS </B></P><P> Public Notice is hereby given that the Council of the City of Ankeny, State of Iowa, will hold a public hearing on the 3rd day of March, 2014, at 5:30 oclock P.M., in the Council Chambers, City Hall, 410 West First Street, Ankeny, Iowa, at which meeting the Council proposes to take action for the issuance of not to exceed $450,000 of General Obligation Bonds, Series 2014 (for a general corporate purpose), bearing interest at the rate of not to exceed nine (9) per centum per annum, the bonds to be issued for the purpose of providing funds to pay costs of the acquisition of real estate for a trail/recreation project jointly and in cooperation with the Polk County Conservation Board and the Iowa National Heritage Foundation.</P><P>At any time before the date of the meeting, a petition, asking that the question of issuing such bonds be submitted to the legal voters of the City, may be filed with the City Clerk of the City in the manner provided by Section 362.4 of the Code of Iowa, pursuant to the provisions of Section 384.26 of the Code of Iowa.</P><P>This Notice is given by order of the City Council of the City of Ankeny, State of Iowa, as provided by Section 384.26 of the Code of Iowa.</P><P>Dated this 17th day of February, 2014.</P><P>City Clerk, City of Ankeny, State of Iowa</P><P>Published in the Des Moines Register on February 21, 2014. </P>\n  '),
('16e06819f325f0b507c680e19f90c31be8491a91', '2014-02-26', '2014-02-27', 'Legals', 'lover, Dave Burgess and Tony Timm. </P><P><B> Approval of the Agenda </B></P><P> Council Member Peterson moved approval, Council Member Butz seconded approval of the agenda. Voice vote passed unanimously. </P><P><B> Good of the Order </B></P><P> Police Chief Dennis McDaniel and Lieutenant Derek Meyer presented the award the department received for National Night Out against crime in August 2013. </P><P><B> Approval of Minutes </B></P><P> Council Member Glover moved to approve the January 6th minutes, Council Member Peterson seconded approval of the minutes. Voice vote passed unanimously. </P><P><B> Public Comment </B></P><P> Mayor Willits thanked everyone for coming to the meetings. No other public comment. </P><P><B> Approval of the Consent Agenda </B></P><P> The Investment Report was removed to the next meeting. Council Member Glover moved to approve, Council Member Butz seconded approval for Claims & Payroll and approval of David Jenison to the Board of Adjustment to fill the unexpired term of William Mech through December 31, 2014. Voice vote passed unanimously. </P><P><B> Consideration of Class E Liquor License Renewal Request- Sams Club #6344 </B></P><P> Council Member Peterson moved to approve, Council Member Burgess seconded. RC Vote passed unanimously. </P><P><B> Consideration of Class E Liquor License Renewal Request- Wal-Mart Supercenter #1764 </B></P><P> Council Member Burgess moved to approve, Council Member Butz seconded. RC Vote passed unanimously. </P><P><B> Consideration of New Special Class C Liquor License Request- City of Windsor Heights (Chamber Event) </B></P><P> Council Member Glover moved to approve, Council Member Timm seconded. RC Vote passed unanimously. Peterson abstained due to being on Chamber Board. </P><P><B> Consideration of approving the General Administrative Services proposal by Simmering Corey in the amount of $17,500 to administer the Citys Community Development Block Grant Housing program </B></P><P> Council Member Glover moved to approve, Council Member Burgess seconded. RC Vote passed unanimously. </P><P><B> Discussion of Capital Requests </B></P><P> The discussion was tabled. The Public Works Committee will bring recommendations to the City Council. </P><P><B> Council Member Comments </B></P><P> Burgess (No comment), Peterson (Thanked Public Works for keeping the streets clear), Butz (No Comment), Glover (Asked the status of the Metro Waste Board; the Mayor is keeping the appointment as is until the new Metro Waste Director is hired), Timm (No Comment). </P><P><B> Mayors Inquiries </B></P><P> The CVB has a new annual report. The IA League of Cities Legislative Lobby Day is February 4th. Please get questions back to CA about the survey that was emailed out. The Mayor made numerous public appearances. Windsor Heights will be featured on Channel 5 News on February 17th on how the City got its name. The next 10/60 meeting is February 20th at 6:00pm at the Community Center. </P><P><B> Adjourn to 6:00pm on Monday February 17, 2014 for the regular meeting of the City Council. </B></P><P> Council Member Burgess moved and Council Member Peterson seconded. Voice vote passed unanimously.</P><P>Diana Willits, Mayor</P><P>ATTEST:</P><P>Jeffrey Allen Fiegenschuh, City Administrator/Clerk </P>\n  '),
