('3b0fae90e06861a4267f9a351b51715cd26c5dc5', '2014-02-26', '2014-02-27', 'Legals', 'to the street grade elevations established in this ordinance:</P><P>a. Datum Plane: All grades are established and described in feet and decimals of feet with respect to a horizontal plane known as the datum plane.</P><P>b. Bench Mark: Bury bolt on hydrant south of NW 36th Street, north side of Fieldstream Plat 1, northeast corner of subdivision. Elevation=980.32.</P><P>c. Grades: The intermediate elevations between the grade points as established shall be straight lines except at the intersection of grade lines where vertical curves shall be used.</P><P>d. Street Grades: Street grade elevations for NW 36th Street shall be along the profile grade line (PGL) at the north curb line of the street unless specifically established otherwise.</P><P>e. Street Stationing: The stationing for NW 36th Street shall commence approximately 185 feet west of the centerline intersection of NW 36th Street/NW Abilene Road. The beginning station shall be 134+84.61 and continue easterly to immediately west of the intersection of NW State Street to station 162+03.00.</P><P>Section 2. Street grades are hereby established as follows:</P><P>NW 36th Street</P><P>Station Elevation</P><P>134+84.61 972.27 VPI</P><P>136+00.00 972.87 VPC</P><P>137+50.00 972.81 VPT</P><P>139+75.00 971.46 VPC</P><P>141+25.00 971.68 VPT</P><P>152+25.00 981.46 VPC</P><P>154+25.00 981.75 VPT</P><P>159+00.00 978.90 VPC</P><P>160+50.00 979.05 VPT</P><P>162+03.00 980.28 VPI</P><P>Section 3. All ordinances or parts of ordinances in conflict with the provisions of this ordinance are hereby repealed.</P><P>Section 4. This ordinance shall be in full force and effect from and after its passage, approval and publication as provided by law.</P><P>PASSED AND APPROVED this 17th day of February, 2014.</P><P>Mayor</P><P>ATTEST:</P><P>City Clerk</P><P>1ST Con 2/3/14</P><P>2nd Con 2/17/14</P><P>3rd Con 2/17/14</P><P>PUBLISHED IN THE DES MOINES REGISTER