('d9b50ca2e4081902d6a33269635c7bd5e51111e1', '2014-02-26', '2014-02-27', 'Legals', 'stated below must be filed before 2:00 p.m. on February 27, 2014 in the office of the City Clerk, Clive City Hall, 1900 NW 114th Street, Clive, Iowa 50325-7077 </P><P><B> Time and Place Sealed Proposals Will be Opened and Considered. </B> Sealed proposals will be opened and bids tabulated at 2:00 p.m. on February 27, 2014, in the Council Chambers of the City Hall for consideration by the Clive City Council at its meeting on March 6, 2014. The City of Clive reserves the right to reject any and all bids. </P><P><B> Time for Commencement and Completion of Work. </B> Work on the improvements shall be commenced upon receipt of the written Notice to Proceed. Assignment of working days and incentive/disincentive clauses associated with work on the project shall be as follows:</P><P>Division 1 - twenty four (24) working days with a six (6) day work week required (M - Sat)</P><P>Division 2 - twenty four (24) working days with a six (6) day work week required (M - Sat)</P><P>Division 3 - twenty six (26) working days with a six (6) day work week required (M - Sat)</P><P>Division 4 - twenty six (26) working days with a six (6) day work week required (M - Sat)</P><P>Working days on each Division will be counted independently of one another and commence when a Division is closed to traffic and vehicular access to individual properties is denied.</P><P>Incentive on each Division - $2,500 per day for each day the work is substantially completed in advance of the working day limit being reached (capped at 5 days maximum).</P><P>Disincentive on each Division - $2,500 per day for each day the work has not reached substantial completion after the working day limit has been reached (capped at 5 days maximum).</P><P>A Division will be considered substantially complete when all work items on the Division have been completed (including restoration/sodding) and the street has been reopened to local traffic. Punch list items not requiring additional street closures may be completed after opening a Division at the discretion of the Jurisdictional Engineer.</P><P>Overall Project Incentive - a one-time lump sum payment of $25,000 if the entire project is completed (including restoration/sodding) and reopened to traffic by 5:00 pm on Friday, August 29, 2014. This is a No Excuses Date independent of the counting of working days and will not be shifted once construction of the project has commenced. There will be no corresponding Disincentive on the overall project.</P><P>No incentives or disincentives will be paid during the 2015 construction season if, for whatever reason, work on the project is not completed in the 2014 calendar year. There are no liquidated damages assigned to this project. </P><P><B> Bid Security. </B> Each bidder shall accompany its bid with bid security as security that the successful bidder will enter into a contract for the work bid upon and will furnish, after the award of contract, a corporate surety bond, in form acceptable to the Jurisdiction, for the faithful performance of the contract, in an amount equal to one hundred percent of the amount of the contract. The bidders security shall be in the amount fixed in the Instruction to Bidders and shall be in the form of a cashiers check, a certified check, or a bank money order drawn on a FDIC insured bank in Iowa or on a FDIC insured bank chartered under the laws of the United States; or a certified share draft drawn on a credit union in Iowa or chartered under the laws of the United States; or a bid bond on the form provided in the contract documents with corporate surety satisfactory to the Jurisdiction. The bid shall contain no condition except as provided in the specifications. </P><P><B> Contract Documents. </B> Copies of the contract documents are available from the Community Development Department and may be examined at the Clive City Hall, 1900 NW 114th Street, Clive, Iowa. Copies shall be available at no cost. Project documents will be on file for inspection at the following offices after issuance date:</P><P>Construction Update Plan Room Network</P><P>Des Moines Office</P><P>221 Park Street</P><P>Des Moines, IA 50303</P><P>(515) 288-8904 or 1-800-362-2578</P><P>McGraw-Hill Plan Room</P><P>4300 Beltway Place, Suite 180</P><P>Arlington, TX 76018</P><P>1-800-328-4542 Ext. 3628 </P><P><B> Public Hearing on Proposed Contract Documents and Estimated Costs for Improvement. </B> A public hearing will be held by the Clive City Council on the proposed contract documents (plans, specifications and form of contract) and estimated cost for the improvements, as bid by the selected bidder, at its meeting at 6:00 pm on March 6, 2014, in said Council Chambers of the City Hall, 1900 NW 114th Street, Clive, Iowa. </P><P><B> Preference of Products and Labor. </B> By virtue of statutory authority, preference will be given to products and provisions grown and coal produced within the State of Iowa, and to Iowa domestic labor, to the extent lawfully required under Iowa statutes. </P><P><B> Sales Tax. </B> The bidder shall include sales tax in the bid. Sales tax exemption certificates will not be issued by the City of Clive. The City will make application for reimbursement of sales tax with the Iowa Department of Revenue at the completion of the project. </P><P><B> General Nature of Public Improvement. </B> This project includes all materials, equipment, transportation and labor needed to remove and reconstruct portions of NW 103rd Street and Lincoln Avenue north of Sunset Terrace and west of NW 100th Street in the City of Clive, Iowa. Project items include excavation, rock subbase, 7" PCC pavement, storm sewer intakes, 6" longitudinal subdrain, sidewalk, driveways, removals, traffic control, mobilization, erosion control and sod. Specific project location along with the kind and approximate quantity of materials to be used shall be as set forth in the Plans and Specifications.</P><P>This notice is given by authority of the City of Clive.</P><P>Joyce A. Cortum, City Clerk </P>\n  '),
