('f2f12418886ca3580e13b5aab48a2fa95f29b58a', '2014-02-26', '2014-02-27', 'Legals', '\n    <P><B> NOTICE OF PUBLIC HEARING </B></P><P> The City Council of the City of Des Moines, Iowa, will hold a public hearing on March 10, 2014, at 5:00 p.m., in the Council Chambers, City Hall, 400 Robert D. Ray Drive, Des Moines, Iowa, to consider the proposed Fourteenth Amendment to the Urban Renewal Plan for the Metro Center Urban Renewal Project (hereinafter referred to as the "Plan"). The Metro Center Urban Renewal Area encompasses an irregularly shaped area that includes the downtown core and the areas surrounding the downtown core.</P><P>The purpose of the proposed Fourteenth Amendment to the Plan is to: (a) approve the Doyle Properties office historic rehabilitation project at 130 East 3rd Street, and the East Village Towers residential, commercial, and skilled nursing renovation project at 600 East 5th Street and update prior approved projects; (b) update disposition parcel and public facilities and improvements maps; and (c) update the Financial Condition Report to reflect the approved projects.</P><P>Any person or organization desiring to be heard, for or against the proposed Fourteenth Amendment, will be afforded an opportunity to be heard at such hearing. Any person or organization desiring to submit written material regarding this matter may direct such written material to the Office of the City Clerk, City Hall, 400 Robert D. Ray Drive, Des Moines, Iowa, prior to the start of the City Council meeting on March 10, 2014, at 4:30 p.m.</P><P>CITY OF DES MOINES, IOWA</P><P>T.M. Franklin Cownie, Mayor</P><P>Published in the Des Moines Register on February 20, 2014 </P>\n  '),
